{
  "stem": "24195.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In June of 1942, at the end of that school year, a new regulation, a new directive came out from the Nazi Education Department that anybody that is half-Jewish can no longer be-- can no longer attend a, you know, high school, a secondary school.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, in fact, you couldn't attend any school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't-- you couldn't even go grade school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the question arises-- what, what could you do?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How could you choose a profession or trade for you-- for the rest of your life, I mean, on the-- when you need an education?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the answer is, you can't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You can't even be an unskilled laborer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is exactly the-- that was exactly what I was told when I was-- when I was called into the dean's office in 1942, in June.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And telling me-- and actually, the dean was very nice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was not-- he probably was a Nazi member, I can't remember.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he was a human person.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he, he-- I really felt that he honestly regretted that he had to tell me that I could no longer attend the school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 81,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he couldn't-- he couldn't do anything about the regulations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, when I was in high school-- and that was already after the, you know, after the war was-- 1940, and '41.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And unfortunately, Germany, at that time, was celebrating one military victory after the other.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The, the German U-boats were sinking, you know, Allied ships in the Atlantic, supplying, you know, England with [GERMAN] and, and military hardware from the United States-- constantly.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, the-- you couldn't listen to the radio.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every, every half an hour, there was a special announcement interrupting the regular program.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Another U-boats had sank another 10, 10 freighters.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 82,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so the-- everybody was charged up in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
